    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available now is a collector-grade 1995 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S), preserved in museum-quality condition. This specimen features the legendary 13B-REW rotary engine, still utilizing its complex sequential twin-turbocharger architecture to provide a seamless transition through the power band. The apex seals show exceptional compression, and the vacuum system is pressurized to factory specifications, ensuring peak volumetric efficiency. Power is delivered through a crisp 5-speed manual gearbox to a Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis retains its telepathic handling characteristics thanks to the original double-wishbone suspension and lightweight aluminum components, all showing zero signs of fatigue or oxidation. This is a turn-key, numbers-matching example for the discerning enthusiast who demands mechanical perfection and uncompromised performance.",
      "price": 48500.0,
